cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.CL

This paper is primarily focused on visual representation learning using deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and a large-scale multi-label image database. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of a distributed deep learning framework for training the CNN model, which could also place it in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of semantic segmentation, which could place it in the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of tags for image annotation, which could place it in the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses transfer learning tasks, which could place it in the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category.
